    "summary": "Using the Calendar Component in Shesha The Calendar component can be found in the Advanced group, or you can search for it directly.",
    "content": "Using the Calendar Component in Shesha The Calendar component can be found in the Advanced group, or you can search for it directly. Add the Calendar Component Drag and drop the Calendar component onto your form Click on the component to open its properties Configure Data Source Open the Data Tab Go to the Data tab in the component properties. Add a Layer Click on Add Layer. Open Layer Settings Click on the settings button to configure the layer. Configure Data Go to the Data tab inside the layer configuration. Choose Data Source Depending on where your events are coming from: Select Entity (recommended if using Shesha-managed data) Or select URL if fetching from an API In this example, an Entity is used. Configure Event Fields Select your source entity Example: ProjectMeetings Set the Event Name Example: Project Meeting Configure required fields: Event Start Time → must map to a datetime field Event End Time → must map to a datetime field Example: startsAtUtc endsAtUtc Save Configuration After completing the setup: Save the configuration The calendar should now display your events. Result Notes Your data source must include both start and end datetime fields Using Entity allows Shesha to handle data fetching automatically Ensure your entity data is populated, otherwise no events will display"
