    "content": "Using the Kanban Component in Shesha To use a Kanban component in Shesha, you must first configure a Data Context, then bind the Kanban to an entity and configure grouping and rendering. Steps Insert Data Context Add a Data Context component and select the entity type. Configure Data Source Go to the Data tab of the Kanban properties: Select Data Source Type → Entity Select your entity Example: ProjectTask Insert Kanban Component Add the Kanban component to your form. Configure Reference List In the Data tab of the Kanban: Select the Reference List for the entity Example: ProjectTaskStatus This defines the columns of the Kanban board. The reference list values will appear as columns: Set Grouping Property Go to the Common tab: Set the Grouping Property This must match the property on your entity that corresponds to the reference list. Example: Reference List: ProjectTaskStatus Grouping Property: status (from ProjectTask) If this is incorrect, no data will be displayed. Create Item Render Form Create a form that will render each Kanban item. Requirements: The form Model Type must match the entity Example: ProjectTask Example form: task-card This form can display fields like: Title Description Assign Render Form In the Common tab of the Kanban: Set Render Form Select your item form Example: task-card Preview Click the Preview icon. The Kanban should display items grouped by status. Notes A Data Context is required before using the Kanban The Grouping Property must match the Reference List The Render Form must use the same Model Type as the entity If any of these are misconfigured, data will not display"
